399 static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
400 static const int kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
401 
402 template <typename T>
403 class WeakCallbackInfo {
404  public:
405  typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
406 
407  WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
408  void* embedder_fields[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback],
409  Callback* callback)
410  : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
411  for (int i = 0; i < kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
412  embedder_fields_[i] = embedder_fields[i];
413  }
414  }
415 
416  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
417  V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
418  V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
419 
420  // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
421  // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
422  // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
423  // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
424  // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
425  // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
426  void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
427 
428  private:
429  Isolate* isolate_;
430  T* parameter_;
431  Callback* callback_;
432  void* embedder_fields_[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback];
433 };
434 
435 
436 // kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
437 // will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
438 // will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
439 // actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
440 // possible to request a second pass callback.
441 enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };

632 template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
633  public:
637  V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
643  template <class S>
644  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
645  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
646  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
647  }
653  template <class S, class M2>
654  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
655  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
656  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
657  }
664  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {
665  Copy(that);
666  }
667  template <class S, class M2>
668  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
669  Copy(that);
670  }
671  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) {
672  Copy(that);
673  return *this;
674  }
675  template <class S, class M2>
676  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
677  Copy(that);
678  return *this;
679  }
685  V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
686  if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
687  }
688 
689  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
690  template <class S>
691  V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(const Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
692 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
693  // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
694  // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
695  if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
696 #endif
697  return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(const_cast<Persistent<S>&>(that));
698  }
699 
700  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
701  template <class S>
702  V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() const { // NOLINT
703  return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
704  }
705 
706  private:
707  friend class Isolate;
708  friend class Utils;
709  template<class F> friend class Local;
710  template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
711  template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
712 
713  explicit V8_INLINE Persistent(T* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) {}
714  V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
715  template<class S, class M2>
716  V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
717 };

1376  CachedData()
1377  : data(nullptr),
1378  length(0),
1379  rejected(false),
1380  buffer_policy(BufferNotOwned) {}
1381 
1382  // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1383  // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1384  // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1385  // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.
1386  CachedData(const uint8_t* data, int length,
1387  BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1388  ~CachedData();
1389  // TODO(marja): Async compilation; add constructors which take a callback
1390  // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1391  const uint8_t* data;
1392  int length;
1393  bool rejected;
1394  BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1395 
1396  // Prevent copying.
1397  CachedData(const CachedData&) = delete;
1398  CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&) = delete;
1399  };

6949 struct JitCodeEvent {
6950  enum EventType {
6951  CODE_ADDED,
6952  CODE_MOVED,
6953  CODE_REMOVED,
6954  CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
6955  CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
6956  CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
6957  };
6958  // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
6959  // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
6960  // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
6961  // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
6962  // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
6963  enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
6964 
6965  // There are two different kinds of JitCodeEvents, one for JIT code generated
6966  // by the optimizing compiler, and one for byte code generated for the
6967  // interpreter. For JIT_CODE events, the |code_start| member of the event
6968  // points to the beginning of jitted assembly code, while for BYTE_CODE
6969  // events, |code_start| points to the first bytecode of the interpreted
6970  // function.
6971  enum CodeType { BYTE_CODE, JIT_CODE };
6972 
6973  // Type of event.
6974  EventType type;
6975  CodeType code_type;
6976  // Start of the instructions.
6977  void* code_start;
6978  // Size of the instructions.
6979  size_t code_len;
6980  // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
6981  Local<UnboundScript> script;
6982  // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
6983  // code line information which is returned from the
6984  // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
6985  // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
6986  void* user_data;
6987 
6988  struct name_t {
6989  // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
6990  // zero-terminated.
6991  const char* str;
6992  // Number of chars in str.
6993  size_t len;
6994  };

6996  struct line_info_t {
6997  // PC offset
6998  size_t offset;
6999  // Code position
7000  size_t pos;
7001  // The position type.
7002  PositionType position_type;
7003  };

7024 enum RAILMode : unsigned {
7025  // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
7026  // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
7027  // Throughput may be throttled.
7028  PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
7029  // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
7030  // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
7031  // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.
7032  PERFORMANCE_ANIMATION,
7033  // Idle performance mode: The embedder is idle. V8 can complete deferred work
7034  // in this mode.
7035  PERFORMANCE_IDLE,
7036  // Load performance mode: In this mode high throughput is provided. V8 may
7037  // turn off latency optimizations.
7038  PERFORMANCE_LOAD
7039 };

8909 template <class T>
8910 class Maybe {
8911  public:
8912  V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
8913  V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
8914 
8918  V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
8919 
8924  V8_INLINE void Check() const {
8925  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
8926  }
8927 
8932  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
8933  if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
8934  return IsJust();
8935  }
8936 
8941  V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
8942  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
8943  return value_;
8944  }
8945 
8950  V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
8951  return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
8952  }
8953 
8954  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
8955  return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
8956  (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
8957  }
8958 
8959  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
8960  return !operator==(other);
8961  }
8962 
8963  private:
8964  Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}
8965  explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value_(true), value_(t) {}
8966 
8967  bool has_value_;
8968  T value_;
8969 
8970  template <class U>
8971  friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
8972  template <class U>
8973  friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
8974 };

8978  return Maybe<T>();

10201 Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
10202 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10203  typedef internal::Address A;
10204  typedef internal::Internals I;
10205  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
10206  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
10207  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
10208  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
10209  if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
10210  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
10211  instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType) {
10212  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
10213  A value = I::ReadRawField<A>(obj, offset);
10214 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
10215  // We read the full pointer value and then decompress it in order to avoid
10216  // dealing with potential endiannes issues.
10217  value = I::DecompressTaggedAnyField(obj, static_cast<int32_t>(value));
10218 #endif
10219  internal::Isolate* isolate =
10220  internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(obj);
10221  A* result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, value);
10222  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
10223  }
10224 #endif
10225  return SlowGetInternalField(index);
10226 }
10227 
10228 
10229 void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
10230 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10231  typedef internal::Address A;
10232  typedef internal::Internals I;
10233  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
10234  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
10235  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
10236  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
10237  if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
10238  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
10239  instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType)) {
10240  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
10241  return I::ReadRawField<void*>(obj, offset);
10242  }
10243 #endif
10244  return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
10245 }

10269  ExternalStringResource* result;

10283 String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
10284  String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
10285  typedef internal::Address A;
10286  typedef internal::Internals I;
10287  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
10288  int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
10289  *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
10290  ExternalStringResourceBase* resource;
10291  if (type == I::kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag ||
10292  type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
10293  void* value = I::ReadRawField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
10294  resource = static_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
10295  } else {
10296  resource = GetExternalStringResourceBaseSlow(encoding_out);
10297  }

10807 int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemory(
10808  int64_t change_in_bytes) {
10809  typedef internal::Internals I;
10810  constexpr int64_t kMemoryReducerActivationLimit = 32 * 1024 * 1024;
10811  int64_t* external_memory = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
10812  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryOffset);
10813  int64_t* external_memory_limit = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
10814  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryLimitOffset);
10815  int64_t* external_memory_at_last_mc =
10816  reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
10817  I::kExternalMemoryAtLastMarkCompactOffset);
10818 
10819  // Embedders are weird: we see both over- and underflows here. Perform the
10820  // addition with unsigned types to avoid undefined behavior.
10821  const int64_t amount =
10822  static_cast<int64_t>(static_cast<uint64_t>(change_in_bytes) +
10823  static_cast<uint64_t>(*external_memory));
10824  *external_memory = amount;
10825 
10826  int64_t allocation_diff_since_last_mc =
10827  static_cast<int64_t>(static_cast<uint64_t>(*external_memory) -
10828  static_cast<uint64_t>(*external_memory_at_last_mc));
10829  // Only check memory pressure and potentially trigger GC if the amount of
10830  // external memory increased.
10831  if (allocation_diff_since_last_mc > kMemoryReducerActivationLimit) {
10832  CheckMemoryPressure();
10833  }
10834 
10835  if (change_in_bytes < 0) {
10836  const int64_t lower_limit = *external_memory_limit + change_in_bytes;
10837  if (lower_limit > I::kExternalAllocationSoftLimit)
10838  *external_memory_limit = lower_limit;
10839  } else if (change_in_bytes > 0 && amount > *external_memory_limit) {
10840  ReportExternalAllocationLimitReached();
10841  }
10842  return *external_memory;
10843 }

10845 Local<Value> Context::GetEmbedderData(int index) {
10846 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10847  typedef internal::Address A;
10848  typedef internal::Internals I;
10849  A ctx = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
10850  A embedder_data =
10851  I::ReadTaggedPointerField(ctx, I::kNativeContextEmbedderDataOffset);
10852  int value_offset =
10853  I::kEmbedderDataArrayHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
10854  A value = I::ReadRawField<A>(embedder_data, value_offset);
10855 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
10856  // We read the full pointer value and then decompress it in order to avoid
10857  // dealing with potential endiannes issues.
10858  value =
10859  I::DecompressTaggedAnyField(embedder_data, static_cast<int32_t>(value));
10860 #endif
10861  internal::Isolate* isolate = internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(
10862  *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this));
10863  A* result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, value);
10864  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
10865 #else
10866  return SlowGetEmbedderData(index);
10867 #endif
10868 }
